e%20are%20two%20things%20in%20particular%20to%20pay%20attention%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20the%20flow%20of%20economic%20data%20cut%20off%20for%20now%20as%20the%20government%20shutdown%20persists%2C%20predicting%20the%20likelihood%20of%20a%20recession%20has%20become%20more%20difficult.%20But%20for%20Thomas%20Simons%2C%20chief%20US%20economist%20at%20Jefferies%2C%20there%20are%20some%20red%20flags%20to%20watch%20for%20that%20could%20provide%20clues%20about%20what's%20around%20the%20corner.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20with%20Business%20Insider%2C%20he%20said%20that%20he's%20not%20currently%20forecasting%20a%20recession%2C%20but%20he's%20watching%20the%20labor%20market%20for%20signs%20of%20distress.%20He%20said%20that%20the%20data%20he%20is%20most%20concerned%20about%20is%20exactly%20that%20which%20has%20been%20stopped%20by%20the%20shutdown%2C%20but%20prior%20to%20that%2C%20he%20saw%20two%20elements%20that%20concerned%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20two%20biggest%20red%20flags%20I%20was%20starting%20to%20see%20that%20were%20making%20me%20more%20and%20more%20concerned%20were%20lower%20participation%20rates%20and%20higher%20unemployment%20rates%20among%20specific%20age%20cohorts%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimons%20highlighted%20two%20age%20groups%3A%20recent%20college%20graduates%20in%20their%20early%2020s%20and%20later%20career%20professionals%20between%2055%20and%2065%2C%20essentially%20opposite%20age%20demographics.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20sees%20a%20troubled%20economy%20in%20which%20younger%20workers%20are%20struggling%20to%20break%20in%2C%20while%20people%20their%20parents'%20age%20are%20facing%20difficulties%20as%20well%20amid%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-job-market-indeed-top-tech-roles-getting-chopped-most-2025-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Erapid%20changes%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20demographics%20suggest%20that%20we're%20not%20really%20getting%20a%20ton%20of%20new%20entrants%2C%20with%20more%20people%20retiring%20rather%20than%20graduating%20from%20school%2C%26quot%3B%20Simons%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20combination%20of%20invisible%20young%20workers%20and%20disappearing%20older%20ones%20could%20lead%20to%20a%20labor%20market%20that%20looks%20stable%20on%20the%20surface%20but%20is%20quietly%20hollowing%20out%20beneath.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20setup%20like%20that%20could%20leave%20the%20economy%20especially%20vulnerable%20to%20a%20downturn%20once%20demand%20starts%20to%20cool%20or%20if%20hiring%20slows%20further.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20young%20workers%20don't%20typically%20have%20enough%20spending%20power%20for%20it%20to%20be%20reflected%20in%20economic%20data%2C%20the%20older%20cohort%20Simons%20highlighted%20could%20pose%20a%20much%20more%20severe%20risk%20to%20growth%20if%20their%20spending%20is%20curtailed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20contrast%20those%20older%20workers%20against%20the%20younger%20ones%2C%20those%20%5Bin%20the%20first%20category%5D%20do%20have%20a%20lot%20more%20spending%20power%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20%5Bolder%20workers%5D%20realize%20actual%20loss%20of%20employment%2C%20it's%20going%20to%20show%20up%20in%20the%20economic%20data%20much%20more%20quickly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESimons%20added%20that%20he%20thinks%20this%20potential%20impact%20has%20been%20hidden%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20workers%20between%20the%20highlighted%20age%20groups%20seem%20to%20be%20doing%20well%20overall.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20he%20added%20that%20it's%20clear%20the%20tail%20ends%20of%20the%20labor%20market%20are%20less%20stable.%20This%20is%20likely%20why%20headline%20employment%20data%20hasn't%20revealed%20a%20major%20downturn%20yet%2C%20though%20the%20cracks%20in%20the%20market%20he%20alludes%20to%20could%20ultimately%20cause%20bigger%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Flabor-market-data-recession-w